Filtering and clustering-related scripts are kept here. 
All scripts are configured for use with the North Carolina State University Bioinformatics Research Center Cluster, which makes use of the SLURM job scheduler.

The following dependencies are needed for scripts pertaining to filtering and clustering:
  GATK v4.5.0.0 (quality metrics table obtainment, quality metrics filtering)
    NOTE: installed on the BRC
  pixy (not for population statistics, just because its dependencies allow for using bgzip and tabix)
    NOTE: not installed on the BRC, I installed it as a conda environment
    pixy documentation is available at: https://pixy.readthedocs.io/en/latest/index.html

The order for running these scripts are as follows:
  1) all scripts within filtering_scripts (initial input script is the SNP VCF generated by D.H.: snps.pass.vcf.gz)
  2) all scripts within clustering_scripts (initial input script is the filtered VCF output by the end of the above step: snps.pass.lowqualfiltered_passed_lowdepthfiltered_passed.vcf.gz)
